'''Kuronuma Shrine''' (くろぬまじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Matsukawa-chō Kanazawa|Q11530303|qid=Q11530303|1=Matsukawa-chō Kanazawa}}, {{ill|lt=Fukushima|Q161176|qid=Q161176|1=Fukushima (city)}}, {{ill|lt=Fukushima Prefecture|Q71707|qid=Q71707|1=Fukushima Prefecture}}. It is said to have been enshrined about 1,300 years ago.

=== Overview ===
* Enshrined deities
** Nunakuratamashiki no Mikoto (= 30th emperor {{ill|lt=Emperor Bidatsu|Q316637|qid=Q316637|1=Emperor Bidatsu}})
** {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Yamato Takeru|1=Yamato Takeru|qid=Q461258}} (Yamatotakeru no Mikoto)
* Shrine rank
** Former district shrine

It is one of the candidate shrines for the "Kuronuma Shrine in Shinobu District, Mutsu Province" named in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}, which is also referenced in classical sources.

It is also known for the "Kanazawa no Hayama Gomori" grand festival, designated by Japan as an {{ill|lt=important intangible folk cultural property|Q6573893|qid=Q6573893|1=National Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property}}.
At the April annual festival, Kuronuma Shrine Twelve Kagura is performed, which is also designated by Fukushima Prefecture as an important intangible folk cultural property.

=== References ===
